  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: b1c3cae70ad8d9641a4b5be915b33736, type: 3}
  m_Name: Lamp3_long4
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  lines:
  - speakerName: Lamp
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Me. He grabbed me. I was not the lamp that got thrown in. I was already
      there. I was literally just existing in the river. I had nothing to do with
      this whole situation. But he lifted me up like I was some prize from a game
      show and started asking people, \u201CDid you drop this golden lamp? Or this
      silver lamp?\u201D"
  - speakerName: Lamp
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "And I was like, first of all, I am not silver. Second, nobody dropped
      me. Third, I am pretty sure this story is supposed to be about an axe. Like,
      I don\u2019t want to be rude, but if you are going to do a famous moral story,
      at least get the object right."
  - speakerName: Lamp
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "So yeah, I panicked. I mean, what was I supposed to do? Just stay there
      and become someone\u2019s reward for being honest? No thank you. I have my
      own life. I have my own plans. I don\u2019t want to be used as some random
      lesson for children about not lying."
  - speakerName: Lamp
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: So I used all my magic, jumped out of his hand, flew out of the water,
      and landed here. And now I am wet, tired, and honestly still kind of offended.
      That is basically what happened.
  options:
  - speakerName: You
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    replyText: ....................
